#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A Free State farmer has been arrested in connection with Tuesday's violence outside the Senekal Magistrate's Court. Protesters stormed the court house where two men were appearing in connection with the murder of farm manager Brendin Horner. READ: Police condemn violent Senekal protests In a statement, police say the 52-year-old will be charged with malicious damage to property and public violence. Police say more arrests are imminent. Watch the video above for more details